<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1226,1755]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1334,1359]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Comments.</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation box="[497,663,1334,1359]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refId="ref21531" refString="Mathur, R. N. (1975) Psyllidae of the Indian subcontinent. Indian Council of Agricultural Research, New Delhi, 429 pp." type="book">Mathur (1975)</bibRefCitation>
, the female holotype (Zoological Survey of India, Kolkata), the only type specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burckhardt &amp; Sharma &amp; Raman" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Crawford" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[373,531,1370,1395]" class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Psylla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simlae">
<emphasis box="[373,531,1370,1395]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Psylla simlae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is severely damaged. Awaiting evidence to the contrary, we assume that Crawford’s and Mathur’s material is conspecific. 
<taxonomicName authority="Kandasamy" authorityName="Kandasamy" authorityYear="1986" box="[718,1014,1406,1431]" class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Psylla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longus">
<emphasis box="[718,872,1406,1431]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Psylla longus</emphasis>
Kandasamy
</taxonomicName>
, also reported from 
<taxonomicName box="[1247,1350,1406,1431]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Bauhinia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1247,1350,1406,1431]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Bauhinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, shares with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burckhardt &amp; Sharma &amp; Raman" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Crawford" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[214,319,1442,1467]" class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Psylla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simlae">
<emphasis box="[214,319,1442,1467]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">P. simlae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the body dimensions, the black genal processes and details of the forewing and 
<taxonomicName box="[1315,1432,1442,1467]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Combretaceae" genus="Terminalia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="20" pageNumber="31" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="genus">terminalia</taxonomicName>
, suggesting they are conspecific. Here we consider 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kandasamy" authorityYear="1986" box="[718,870,1478,1503]" class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Psylla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longus">
<emphasis box="[718,870,1478,1503]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Psylla longus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burckhardt &amp; Sharma &amp; Raman" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Crawford" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[1110,1207,1478,1503]" class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Psylla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simlae">
<emphasis box="[1110,1207,1478,1503]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">P. simlae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1226,1755]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Originally described in 
<taxonomicName box="[479,549,1514,1539]" class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Psylla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[479,549,1514,1539]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Psylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this species is not congeneric with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[988,1324,1514,1539]" class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Psylla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alni">
<emphasis box="[988,1114,1514,1539]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Psylla alni</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[1134,1316,1514,1539]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refId="ref20952" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1758) Systema naturae per regna tri naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locis. Impensis Direct. Laurentii Salvii, Holmiae (Stockholm), 824 pp." type="book">Linnaeus, 1758</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, the type species of 
<taxonomicName box="[281,351,1550,1575]" class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Psylla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[281,351,1550,1575]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Psylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. With 
<taxonomicName authority="Heslop-Harrison, 1961" authorityName="Heslop-Harrison" authorityYear="1961" box="[440,854,1550,1575]" class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Psylla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="primitiva">
<emphasis box="[440,576,1551,1574]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">P. primitiva</emphasis>
Heslop-Harrison, 1961
</taxonomicName>
, the type-species of 
<emphasis box="[1108,1317,1550,1575]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Palaeolindergiella</emphasis>
, it shares following characters: head weakly inclined from longitudinal body axis; median suture on vertex developed; genal processes less than 0.8 times as long as vertex along mid-line; preocular sclerite absent; basal spine of metatibia prominent; forewing with broad and often short pterostigma; female 
<taxonomicName box="[920,1034,1658,1683]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Combretaceae" genus="Terminalia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="20" pageNumber="31" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="genus">terminalia</taxonomicName>
long, proctiger cuneate; circumanal ring oval. For this reason, it is formally transferred here to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heslop-Harrison" authorityYear="1961" box="[848,1071,1694,1719]" class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Palaeolindbergiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[848,1071,1694,1719]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Palaeolindbergiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Crawford, 1912)" authorityName="Burckhardt &amp; Sharma &amp; Raman" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Crawford" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[1115,1431,1694,1719]" class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Psylla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simlae" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1115,1216,1694,1719]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">P. simlae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[1237,1424,1694,1719]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refId="ref18783" refString="Crawford, D. L. (1912) Indian Psyllidae. Records of the Indian Museum, 7, 419 - 435." type="journal article">Crawford, 1912</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,279,1730,1755]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,1730,1755]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">comb. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
from 
<taxonomicName box="[348,418,1730,1755]" class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Psylla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[348,418,1730,1755]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Psylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
